         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>This finding aid, created before the advent of computer-generated files, has been converted into a ASCII data file by means of scanning and Optical Character Recognition software. While attempts have been made to retain the complete information from the original document a number of format changes have been made to present the structure of this archive in accordance with current practice.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_0adb99dd056377fb3718a93c6346d914">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Notes and collations for <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>King Lear</part>
            </title>, <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Measure for Measure</part>
            </title>, <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Henry V</part>
            </title>, and <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Two Gentlemen of Verona</part>
            </title>. Textual notes and documents related to editing Shakespeare. Correspondence 1904-10, to David Nichol Smith and Walter Raleigh.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
